        <p>There are 2<italic>n</italic><sup>3</sup>−<italic>n</italic><sup>2</sup>,<italic>n</italic>(<italic>n</italic>−1)(<italic>n</italic>−2)(<italic>n</italic>−3),2<italic>n</italic>(<italic>n</italic>−1) and 4<italic>n</italic>(<italic>n</italic>−1)(<italic>n</italic>−2) items for the four conditions respectively. We can further separate (12) into 16 components and calculate their values under different conditions. The derivation is straightforward. Our conclusion thus holds. □</p>
